        description: "The GEO Landing Page Generator enables users to create AI-optimized landing pages designed for Generative Engine Optimization (GEO) and Answer Engine Optimizati",
        searchText: "GEO Landing Page Generator The GEO Landing Page Generator enables users to create AI-optimized landing pages designed for Generative Engine Optimization (GEO) and Answer Engine Optimization (AEO). By analyzing the target keyword and website, the tool generates a complete landing page with SEO-friendly content, structured sections, and editable HTML that can be published directly to supported CMS platforms. Create Landing Page The Create Landing Page section allows users to generate AI-powered landing pages by providing the required information. Target Keyword Users must enter the primary keyword they want the landing page to rank for. The target keyword is used to: Define the landing page topic. Generate GEO-optimized content. Optimize headings and page structure. Improve ranking across search engines and AI platforms. Website URL Users must provide the website URL The system analyzes the website to understand: Business niche. Brand identity. Website content. Design preferences. This information helps generate a landing page aligned with the business. Content Language Users can specify the language in which the landing page should be generated. Supported examples include: English Spanish French Dutch If no language is provided, the landing page is generated in English by default. Landing Page Generator Users can choose the AI model used to generate the landing page. Available options include: Gemini (Default) Claude (if available) Different models may provide variations in content quality and writing style. Create Landing Page After entering the required information, users can click Create Landing Page. The system generates: GEO & AEO optimized landing page. Structured webpage content. AI-friendly layout. Editable HTML. Search-optimized headings and sections. Design Template After generation, the system automatically applies a landing page template. The template is selected based on: Website branding. Available website styles. Layout preferences. If the website theme cannot be detected, the system applies a default optimized template while maintaining keyword relevance. Save to Project Generated landing pages are automatically associated with the selected project. Users can continue editing the landing page at any time before publishing. Site URL for Publish (Optional) Users can optionally provide a publishing URL. This URL overrides the default project URL when publishing to supported CMS platforms such as: WordPress Webflow Generated Landing Page The Generated Landing Page section displays the complete AI-generated landing page in an editable preview. Users can review and modify the page before publishing. Landing Page Content The landing page contains structured sections optimized for SEO, GEO, and AI search visibility. Typical sections include: Hero Section Primary Heading (H1) Introduction Benefits Features Call-to-Action (CTA) Supporting Content Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs) Conclusion Preview The Preview option displays the landing page in a visual webpage format. Users can review: Layout Typography Content structure Overall appearance before publishing. Code The Code option switches from the visual preview to the HTML source. Users can: View generated HTML. Edit page markup. Copy raw HTML. Integrate with custom websites or CMS platforms. Regenerate Users can click Regenerate to create a new version of the landing page. The system generates fresh content while maintaining the selected keyword and website context. Copy Users can click Copy to copy the generated landing page content or HTML to the clipboard. This allows quick integration into external editors or CMS platforms. Save Users can click Save to store the generated landing page within the selected project. Saved landing pages remain available for future editing and publishing. AI-Optimized Landing Page Structure The generated landing page follows a structured layout designed for both traditional search engines and AI-powered answer engines. The content may include: SEO-optimized Headings AI Summary Section Value Proposition Service or Product Overview Benefits Features Call-to-Action Buttons Supporting Information FAQs Contact or Conversion Sections This structure improves readability, user engagement, and AI discoverability. GEO Tip The information banner at the top of the page explains how to use the GEO Landing Page Generator. It highlights: Enter a target keyword and website URL. Generate GEO & AEO optimized landing pages. Customize the generated layout. Publish directly to supported CMS platforms. Improve visibility across AI-powered search engines.",
