        slug: "ai-visibility-tracker",
        title: "AI Visibility Tracker",
        description: "The AI Visibility Tracker helps users monitor how their brand appears across leading AI search platforms and Large Language Models (LLMs), including ChatGPT, Ge",
        searchText: "AI Visibility Tracker The AI Visibility Tracker helps users monitor how their brand appears across leading AI search platforms and Large Language Models (LLMs), including ChatGPT, Gemini, Claude, Perplexity, and Grok. It identifies the prompts where the brand is mentioned, tracks AI visibility over time, and helps users measure the impact of their Generative Engine Optimization (GEO) efforts. Select Project Users can select an existing project or website from the dropdown list. The selected project is used to: Load previously saved AI visibility results. Perform a new AI visibility analysis. Track prompt-level brand mentions. New Monitor Users can click New Monitor to start a fresh AI visibility analysis. The system scans supported AI platforms to identify: Prompts where the brand appears. Brand mentions across different AI models. Current AI search visibility. Analysis Status The analysis status displays the progress of the latest AI visibility scan. It includes: Last Analysis Date and Time. Analysis Completion Status. Confirmation that saved results have been loaded. Search History The Search History section stores all previous AI visibility analyses. Each history entry displays: Analysis Date and Time. Website URL. Number of Prompts Analyzed. Number of AI Models Checked. Saved Prompt Count. Users can reopen previous analyses without running a new scan. AI Visibility Results The AI Visibility Results section provides a summary of the latest AI visibility analysis. URLs in Sitemap Displays the total number of website URLs included in the analysis. This metric represents the sampled pages used during AI visibility evaluation. Prompts Your Brand Showing For Displays the total number of prompts where the selected brand is currently mentioned across supported AI platforms. This helps users understand how frequently their brand appears in AI-generated responses. Brand Host Displays the primary website or domain being monitored during the AI visibility analysis. This identifies the brand associated with the current results. Prompts Your Brand Showing For This section lists all prompts where the selected brand is currently being mentioned by AI platforms. Each entry represents a search query or user prompt for which the brand appears in AI-generated responses. The prompt list helps users: Discover AI search opportunities. Understand how users interact with AI platforms. Identify topics where the brand is already visible. Find content gaps for additional GEO optimization. Prompt List Each prompt entry displays: Prompt Number Prompt Text Examples include: Best Generative Engine Optimization tools Best SEO tools Webflow SEO optimization Technical GEO in SEO AI SEO writer tools Users can use these prompts to create optimized blogs, landing pages, FAQs, and supporting content that improve AI visibility. GEO Tip The information banner at the top of the page explains how to use the AI Visibility Tracker. It highlights: Enter a website URL to analyze AI visibility. Track prompts where the brand appears across ChatGPT, Gemini, Claude, Perplexity, and Grok. Monitor changes in AI visibility over time. Measure the effectiveness of GEO optimization efforts.",
