        description: "The GEO Crawl feature analyzes a website's internal linking structure to identify crawlability issues, orphan pages, and optimization opportunities. It crawls t",
        searchText: "GEO Crawl The GEO Crawl feature analyzes a website's internal linking structure to identify crawlability issues, orphan pages, and optimization opportunities. It crawls the website, evaluates how pages are interconnected, and provides actionable insights to improve website structure, accessibility, and Generative Engine Optimization (GEO). Website Internal Link Analysis The Website Internal Link Analysis section allows users to crawl a website and analyze its internal linking architecture. The crawler scans website pages to discover: Internal linking patterns. Orphan pages. Crawl depth. Link distribution. Internal linking opportunities. The crawler supports analysis of up to 100 pages per crawl. Website Crawler Users can select an existing project or enter a website URL to begin the crawl. The input field supports: Selecting a saved project. Entering a website URL manually. Searching for an existing project. The selected website becomes the source for the crawl analysis. Start Crawl After selecting a project or entering a website URL, users can click Start Crawl to begin the analysis. The crawler scans the website and evaluates: Internal page links. Crawl depth. Orphan pages. Internal link distribution. Website accessibility. Crawl Status During and after the crawl, the system displays the crawl status. The status includes: Crawl progress. Number of pages crawled. Analysis completion status. Saved crawl results. Search Results After the crawl is complete, the system displays a crawl summary including: Total Pages Crawled. Internal Links Found. Orphan Pages Detected. Maximum Crawl Depth. Internal Linking Score. Export CSV Users can export the complete crawl report as a CSV file for reporting or additional analysis. Download White-Label Report Users can download a professional White-Label Report containing the complete crawl analysis for client presentations and documentation. Internal Linking Analysis Report The Internal Linking Analysis Report provides a detailed overview of the website's internal linking performance. The report includes: Pages Crawled. Internal Links. Orphan Pages. Website Structure Metrics. Overview The Overview tab summarizes the overall crawl results. It displays the following metrics: Total Pages Displays the total number of pages successfully crawled during the analysis. Internal Links Displays the total number of internal links discovered between website pages. Internal links help search engines and AI crawlers understand website structure and improve content discoverability. Orphan Pages Displays the number of orphan pages detected. Orphan pages are pages that do not receive internal links from other pages on the website, making them difficult for search engines and AI crawlers to discover. Maximum Depth Displays the deepest crawl level reached from the homepage. Lower crawl depth generally improves accessibility and page discoverability. Quick Stats The Quick Stats section provides additional crawl statistics. It includes: Average Internal Links Per Page Displays the average number of internal links available on each crawled page. External Links Found Displays the number of external links identified during the crawl. Internal Link Density Measures the percentage of internal links relative to the total links found on the website. Higher internal link density generally improves crawlability and content discovery. Link Structure The Link Structure tab provides a detailed view of how website pages are connected through internal links. Users can analyze: Parent and child page relationships. Internal linking paths. Link distribution across pages. Crawl hierarchy. This helps identify opportunities to improve navigation and strengthen page authority. Orphan Pages The Orphan Pages tab lists pages that have no incoming internal links. For each orphan page, users can identify: Page URL. Crawl status. Link availability. The report helps users connect isolated pages to the rest of the website and improve discoverability. Scoring The Scoring tab evaluates the website's internal linking quality using multiple crawl metrics. The analysis considers: Internal link coverage. Crawl depth. Link distribution. Website accessibility. Overall internal linking quality. A higher score indicates a stronger internal linking structure and better crawl efficiency. Fix The Fix tab provides AI-generated recommendations to improve the website's internal linking architecture. Recommendations may include: Add internal links to orphan pages. Improve navigation between related pages. Reduce crawl depth. Increase internal link coverage. Connect isolated content. Improve page hierarchy. Optimize website structure for better crawlability. These recommendations help improve both traditional SEO and Generative Engine Optimization (GEO). GEO Tip The information banner at the top of the page explains how to use the GEO Crawl feature. It highlights: Start the crawl using a website URL or project. Analyze internal linking structure and crawl depth. Identify orphan pages and crawl issues. Follow the recommended fixes to improve website accessibility and AI discoverability.",
