        description: "The Reports page provides a centralized dashboard for monitoring GEO, AI visibility, content generation, and website performance metrics over a selected time pe",
        searchText: "Reports The Reports page provides a centralized dashboard for monitoring GEO, AI visibility, content generation, and website performance metrics over a selected time period. Users can filter reports by project and date range to analyze trends, measure optimization progress, and export data for reporting. Project Selection Users can select a project from the Select Project dropdown. All report data, charts, and analytics are filtered based on the selected project. Date Range Filter Users can customize the reporting period by selecting: Start Date End Date The dashboard automatically refreshes all charts and metrics based on the selected date range. Users can also click Reset to Last 30 Days to quickly restore the default reporting period. Traffic from AI Engines Displays combined traffic received from AI platforms over time. Supported platforms include: ChatGPT Gemini Claude Perplexity The line chart helps users monitor AI-driven website traffic trends across the selected date range. Blogs Written Displays the number of AI-generated blog posts created during the selected reporting period. The chart helps users track content production activity over time. Blogs Published Shows how many generated blog posts have been published. This helps measure publishing consistency and content deployment. Landing Pages Created Displays the total number of AI-generated landing pages created within the selected time period. The graph visualizes landing page creation trends. Landing Pages Published Shows the number of generated landing pages that have been published. This enables users to compare created versus published landing pages. GEO Crawl Score Over Time Displays historical GEO Crawl Scores collected from website crawl analyses. The chart helps users monitor improvements or declines in crawl health over time. Score Breakdown Provides a visual breakdown of the GEO Crawl Score across multiple scoring categories. Categories include: Link Density Anchor Text Quality Navigation Structure Contextual Relevance Orphan Page Penalty The chart helps users identify which factors contribute most to the overall crawl score. Select Pages for GEO Score Report Users can search and select one or more website pages. After selecting pages, the report focuses on GEO performance metrics for those specific URLs. Page GEO Scores Displays GEO scores for individual website pages. The bar chart allows users to: Compare page performance. Identify high-performing pages. Detect pages requiring optimization. Monitor GEO score consistency across the website. Interactive Charts All report visualizations are automatically updated when: The selected project changes. The date range changes. New analysis data becomes available. This provides an up-to-date view of website performance. Report Insights The Reports dashboard helps users analyze: AI search traffic trends. Content generation activity. Content publishing performance. GEO crawl improvements. Individual page GEO scores. Website optimization progress. Historical performance comparisons. GEO Tip The information banner at the top of the page explains how to use the Reports dashboard. It highlights: Filter reports using custom date ranges. Compare GEO metrics across different time periods. Export report data for stakeholders. Track AI visibility and GEO performance over time. Measure optimization progress using historical analytics.",
