        description: "The Campaigns module allows users to create and manage backlink outreach campaigns. Each campaign organizes backlink opportunities by website, target keyword, a",
        searchText: "Campaigns The Campaigns module allows users to create and manage backlink outreach campaigns. Each campaign organizes backlink opportunities by website, target keyword, and outreach settings, making it easier to track link-building activities. Campaign Overview The Campaigns page displays all created backlink campaigns and their associated information. The page includes: Campaign Name Website URL Target Keyword Number of Opportunities Campaign Status Delete Campaign option If no campaigns exist, users can create a new campaign using the Create Campaign button. Create Campaign Creating a campaign is a guided four-step process. Step 1: Campaign Details Configure the basic information for the campaign. Campaign Name Enter a unique name to identify the campaign. Example: Q1 Backlink Push Your Name Enter the name that will be used as the sign-off in generated outreach emails. Example: Alex Chen Campaign Language Select the language that will be used for: Google search results AI-generated outreach emails Campaign communication Step 2: Website URL Enter the website URL that will be promoted through the backlink campaign. Website URL Enter the full website address Example: https://example.com The system uses this URL to discover backlink opportunities and generate outreach recommendations. Step 3: Target Keyword Select the primary keyword for the campaign. The system automatically extracts keywords from the website and suggests them as keyword options. Suggested Keywords Displays keyword suggestions identified from the website. Examples: AI SEO platform GEO visibility tool Backlink management software SEO content platform Content optimization AI Local SEO platform with AI Custom Keyword Users can manually enter their own keyword if it is not listed in the suggestions. Example: best project management software Step 4: Opportunities The platform begins searching Google results and identifying potential backlink opportunities for the selected keyword. The opportunities discovery process includes: Finding websites ranking for the keyword Identifying guest post opportunities Discovering resource pages Finding competitor backlinks Identifying outreach prospects Create Campaign Once all steps are completed, clicking Create Campaign saves the campaign and starts backlink opportunity discovery. The created campaign includes: Campaign Name Website URL Target Keyword Opportunity Count Campaign List The Campaigns page displays all existing campaigns in a centralized dashboard. Each campaign card shows: Campaign Name The user-defined campaign identifier Website URL The website associated with the campaign. Target Keyword The primary keyword being targeted Opportunities Count Displays the total number of discovered backlink opportunities. Delete Campaign Permanently removes the selected campaign and its associated data. Campaign Management Features The Campaigns module enables users to: Create multiple backlink campaigns Organize campaigns by website and keyword Discover backlink opportunities automatically Track opportunities for each campaign Manage and delete campaigns Centralize outreach activities in one workspace Campaign Workflow Create Campaign ↓ Enter Campaign Details ↓ Add Website URL ↓ Select Target Keyword ↓ Discover Opportunities ↓ Launch Backlink Outreach Campaign",
