        searchText: "Knowledge Base The Knowledge Base module allows users to add, manage, and organize information that powers chatbot responses. Knowledge can be added by scraping website content or manually entering text. The chatbot uses this information to answer user questions accurately and provide contextual responses. Add New Knowledge The platform supports two methods for creating knowledge sources: 1. From URL 2. From Text Add Knowledge From URL The From URL option allows users to train the chatbot using website content. Website URL Enter the website URL that you want the chatbot to learn from. Example https://blazly.ai Add Website Click Add Website to start the website indexing process. What Happens 1. Website URL is validated. 2. The platform crawls and scrapes the website. 3. Website pages are indexed. 4. Knowledge becomes available to the chatbot. Website Scraping Status During indexing, the platform displays the progress message: Scraping your site (up to 5 min)... The scraping time may vary depending on: Website size Number of pages Website response speed Content complexity Successful Website Indexing After completion, the platform displays a confirmation message. Example: Website updated successfully. Scraped 15 pages from your sitemap. Indexing for fast chat in the background. Add Knowledge From Text The From Text option allows users to manually create knowledge entries. Title Enter a name for the knowledge entry Purpose Organize knowledge sources. Easily identify information later. Content Enter or paste text that should be used by the chatbot. Examples: FAQs Company information Product descriptions Policies Support documentation Internal instructions Add Knowledge Click Add Knowledge to save the content and make it available to the chatbot. Knowledge History The Knowledge History section displays all previously added knowledge sources. Information Displayed Each knowledge source includes: Knowledge title Source URL Storage size Number of indexed pages Creation date Actions Open Knowledge View the complete knowledge source and its details. Delete Knowledge Remove the knowledge source from the platform. Knowledge History Example Blazly GEO — Generative Engine Optimization | Blazly AI https://www.blazly.ai 67 KB • 15 pages Supported Knowledge Types Website URLs Automatically scrape and index websites Manual Text Add custom content directly Knowledge Workflow Website Knowledge Select From URL ↓ Enter Website URL ↓ Click Add Website ↓ Website Scraping Starts ↓ Pages Indexed ↓ Knowledge Added Text Knowledge Select From Text ↓ Enter Title ↓ Add Content ↓ Click Add Knowledge ↓ Knowledge Saved",
