        searchText: "All Leads The All Leads module provides a centralized location to view and manage every lead captured through your chatbots. Whenever a visitor shares their information or interacts with your chatbot, their details are automatically stored here for follow-up and qualification. Lead Statistics At the top of the page, the system displays: New Leads Shows the number of newly captured leads. Qualified Leads Shows the number of leads that have been marked as qualified. Example: New: 0 Qualified: 0 Refresh Leads The Refresh button reloads the latest lead data. Purpose Fetch newly captured leads. Update lead statuses. Synchronize lead information. Lead Capture Sources Leads are automatically created when visitors: Enter their email before chatting. Fill custom visitor fields. Request human assistance. Interact with the chatbot widget. Lead Information Each lead can include: Name Email address Phone number Company Website Custom fields Chat history Lead score Lead status Chatbot source Lead Lifecycle Visitor opens chatbot ↓ Provides contact information ↓ Starts conversation ↓ Lead is created ↓ Stored in All Leads ↓ Qualified and assigned Lead Statuses Leads can progress through different stages: New Qualified Assigned Contacted Converted Empty State When there are no captured leads, the page displays: No Leads Yet Leads will appear here once users start chatting with your chatbots Integration with Other Modules The All Leads module works together with: Inbox Access visitor conversations and continue communication. Lead Management Organize and manage captured leads Lead Scoring Automatically score leads based on engagement and collected information. Analytics Track lead generation performance and conversion metrics. Lead Qualification Leads can be qualified using: Collected email address Conversation activity Visitor information Chat engagement Lead score Custom qualification rules",
