        slug: "lead-scoring",
        title: "Lead Scoring",
        description: "The Lead Scoring module allows you to automatically assign scores to leads based on their engagement and behavior during chatbot conversations. Scores help iden",
        searchText: "Lead Scoring The Lead Scoring module allows you to automatically assign scores to leads based on their engagement and behavior during chatbot conversations. Scores help identify high-intent visitors and prioritize follow-ups. Save Rules The Save Rules button applies and stores all lead scoring configurations. Base Score & Interest Levels Base Score (0–100) The starting score assigned to every new lead before additional rules are applied. Example: Base score: 10 Medium Interest From Defines the minimum score required for a lead to be classified as Medium Interest. Example: 40 High Interest From Defines the minimum score required for a lead to be classified as High Interest. Example: 70 Lead Categories Cold Leads 0 – 39 Low engagement and low purchase intent Medium Interest Leads 40 – 69 Moderate engagement and potential buying interest. High Interest Leads 70 – 100 Highly engaged prospects with strong conversion potential. Scoring Rules Rules add points on top of the base score. Formula Final Score = Base Score + Rule Points Maximum score: 100 Rule Components Each rule contains: Enable/Disable option Rule Name Rule Type Points to Add Additional conditions Add Rule Click: + Add Rule to create a custom scoring rule. Rule Types 1. Email Provided Adds points when a visitor provides an email address. Configuration Rule Name Points to add Example Provided email address +15 points 2. Keyword Match Adds points when visitor messages contain predefined keywords. Configuration Rule Name Keywords Points to add Example Purchase intent keywords +35 points Keywords: buy pricing cost purchase demo trial Product Interest Keywords Example: feature compare integration support plan Points: +20 points 3. Message Count Adds points based on visitor engagement level. Configuration Minimum visitor messages Points to add Example Engaged Conversation 3+ visitor messages +15 points Deep Conversation 6+ visitor messages +10 points Enable or Disable Rules Each rule includes an Enabled checkbox When enabled: Rule contributes to scoring. When disabled: Rule is ignored. Delete Rule Each rule includes a delete icon that allows administrators to remove unwanted scoring rules. Example Scoring Calculation Visitor Actions Base Score = 10 Provided Email = +15 Purchase Intent Keywords = +35 3+ Messages = +15 Final Score 10 + 15 + 35 + 15 = 75 Result: High Interest Lead Sample Lead Journey Visitor starts chat ↓ Base score assigned ↓ Rules are evaluated ↓ Points added ↓ Final score calculated ↓ Lead categorized",
