        title: "Brand Repository",
        description: "The Brand Repository serves as the central location for storing brand assets that are used throughout Blazly Social. It allows users to upload their brand logo ",
        searchText: "Brand Repository The Brand Repository serves as the central location for storing brand assets that are used throughout Blazly Social. It allows users to upload their brand logo and define brand color palettes, ensuring that AI-generated content and visual assets remain consistent with the organization's branding guidelines. The stored brand assets are automatically used as contextual inputs during content and image generation, helping maintain visual consistency across social media posts. Logo Management The Logo section allows users to upload and manage their brand logo for use across AI-generated social media content. Logo Upload Users can upload a brand logo that will be stored within the Brand Repository. Supported functionality includes: Uploading a new logo. Replacing an existing logo. Managing a single primary brand logo. Replace Logo The Replace Logo option allows users to update the currently stored logo without modifying other brand settings. When a new logo is uploaded: The previous logo is replaced. Future AI-generated content uses the updated logo. Brand references are automatically refreshed across image generation workflows. Logo-Based AI Context The uploaded logo is used as a visual reference during image generation. This enables Blazly Social to: Incorporate brand identity into generated visuals. Maintain consistency across marketing assets. Align generated imagery with existing brand elements. Supported Logo Formats Logo uploads support common image formats such as: PNG JPG/JPEG The uploaded logo must be accessible for AI processing during image generation workflows. Brand Colors The Brand Colors section allows users to define their official brand color palette. These colors are used as contextual guidance during visual content generation to ensure generated assets align with brand identity. Color Palette Management Users can store up to five brand colors within the repository. Each color can be configured individually using: Color Picker Hexadecimal Color Code Color Fields The repository supports: Color 1 Color 2 Color 3 Color 4 Color 5 Each field represents a brand color that can be referenced during content generation. Hex Color Codes Users can manually enter hexadecimal color values. Examples: #1E293B #0F172A #2563EB This allows precise control over brand color definitions. Color Preview Each color field includes a visual preview box that displays the selected color in real time. This helps users verify their selected palette before saving. Save Colors The Save Colors action stores the configured color palette and makes it available across the platform. Once saved: Brand colors become part of the repository. Future AI-generated visuals can reference the selected palette. Color preferences remain available for future content creation sessions. Brand Asset Utilization The assets stored within the Brand Repository are automatically available across Blazly Social. AI Image Generation Support When generating social media visuals, Blazly Social can utilize: Uploaded brand logo. Brand color palette. Visual branding preferences. Consistent Brand Identity The repository helps ensure that generated content maintains: Consistent visual appearance. Brand recognition. Uniform color usage. Cohesive social media branding. The Brand Repository acts as the centralized branding system that enables Blazly Social to generate content that aligns closely with an organization's visual identity.",
