        searchText: "Your Posts The Your Posts page displays all posts created or scheduled within Blazly Social. It serves as a centralized location where users can view and manage posts generated through Create Post, Social Autopilot, and the Calendar. Users can review post details, monitor publishing status, and filter posts by social media platform. Social App Filter The Social App dropdown allows users to filter posts by connected social media platform. Available options include: All Platforms Instagram Facebook LinkedIn Twitter (X) Threads Selecting a platform displays only the posts associated with that social media account. Refresh Click Refresh to load the latest posts and update the page with any newly created, scheduled, or published content. Post Status Each post includes a status that indicates its current publishing stage. Common statuses include: Draft – The post has been created but has not been published. Scheduled – The post is scheduled to be published at a specified date and time. Published – The post has been successfully published to the selected platform. Scheduled Date and Time Each scheduled post displays its planned publishing date and time, allowing users to monitor upcoming content. Post Content The post preview displays the content that will be or has been published. This may include: Caption or text Emojis Hashtags Mentions Formatting Users can review the content before publication. Media Preview If a post contains media, a preview is displayed alongside the post. Supported media types include: Images Graphics Promotional banners Other uploaded visual content This allows users to verify that the correct media is attached to the post. Draft Management Draft posts can be reopened for further editing. Click Open Draft to: Modify the post content. Update attached media. Change the scheduled publishing date and time. Save the updated draft or schedule it for publishing. Autopilot Drafts The page also displays the number of posts generated by Social Autopilot that are currently saved as drafts.",
