        searchText: "Brain Located in the left navigation menu under the Strategy section. Used to create, store, organize, and manage knowledge that can be reused across Blazly's content generation features. Brain allows users to build a centralized knowledge repository containing research, notes, competitor analysis, brand guidelines, content briefs, and reference materials. Saved knowledge can be reused to improve content relevance, consistency, and contextual accuracy during blog generation and bulk content creation. Features Add Knowledge Allows users to create new knowledge entries that can be stored within the Brain knowledge base for future use. Document Name Defines the title or identifier for the knowledge entry. This helps users organize, categorize, and quickly locate saved information within the knowledge base. Content Editor Provides a rich text editing environment where users can create, paste, edit, and organize content before saving it to the knowledge base. The editor can be used to store: Research notes Competitor analysis Content briefs Brand guidelines Product information Industry insights SEO strategies Reference materials Rich Text Formatting The editor supports various formatting options to help structure and organize knowledge effectively. Supported formatting options include: Bold Italics Underline Strikethrough Hyperlinks Heading 1 (H1) Heading 2 (H2) Heading 3 (H3) Heading 4 (H4) Ordered Lists Unordered Lists Text Alignment Undo Redo Save to Knowledge Base Stores the current document and its content within Brain, making it available for future reference and content generation workflows. Saved Knowledge Displays all previously saved knowledge documents within the knowledge base. Users can review and access stored information whenever needed. Saved Items Counter Displays the total number of knowledge documents currently stored in Brain, providing a quick overview of the user's knowledge repository. Knowledge Management Brain acts as a centralized repository where users can continuously build and expand their content knowledge base. Users can save: Topic research Competitor research Brand messaging Product documentation Content frameworks Customer personas Marketing strategies SEO insights Industry trends Internal documentation This information remains accessible for future content creation activities.",
