        searchText: "Saved Strategies Located in the left navigation menu under the Strategy section. Saved Strategies acts as a centralized repository for all content strategies generated through Strategy Builder. It allows users to store, manage, revisit, and execute previously created SEO content plans without rebuilding them from scratch. Features Strategy Repository Stores all saved content strategies generated from the Strategy Builder. Both standard and enhanced strategies can be accessed from a single location for future reference and implementation. Saved Strategy Library Displays a collection of previously saved strategies. Each saved strategy contains: Target keyword Pillar topic Cluster topics Keyword recommendations Suggested word counts Publishing schedule Strategy creation details Strategy Access Allows users to reopen saved strategies at any time. This enables teams to review content plans, analyze topic structures, and continue execution without regenerating the strategy. Strategy Management Provides a centralized workspace for organizing and managing content strategies. Users can: View saved strategies Review content plans Continue strategy execution Access planning data for future campaigns Create New Strategy The Create New Strategy button allows users to quickly navigate back to Strategy Builder and generate a new content strategy. This helps users create additional content roadmaps for different keywords, products, services, or marketing campaigns. Strategy Persistence Saved strategies remain available for future use, allowing users to build long-term SEO and content marketing plans without losing previous research and planning efforts. Empty State When no strategies have been saved, the page displays a No Saved Strategies message along with a Build a Strategy action button. This provides a direct path to Strategy Builder where users can generate and save their first content strategy.",
