        searchText: "SEO Audit Located in the Analyze section of the left navigation menu. SEO Audit helps users evaluate the overall SEO health of their website by analyzing data connected through Google Search Console. It provides actionable insights into search performance, indexing status, technical SEO issues, and optimization opportunities. The audit system is designed to identify areas that may impact search visibility, rankings, and organic traffic growth, allowing users to prioritize improvements based on real website performance data. Features Google Search Console Integration SEO Audit requires a connected Google Search Console property to access website performance and indexing data. The integration enables Blazly to: Retrieve verified website data Analyze search performance metrics Access indexing information Evaluate SEO health across connected properties Generate audit reports based on real search data Users can connect their Search Console property through the Integrations section. SEO Health Analysis The audit engine evaluates multiple SEO factors across the connected website. The analysis may include: Indexing status Search visibility Page performance Technical SEO signals Content optimization opportunities Crawlability insights Search Console issue detection This provides a centralized overview of website SEO performance. Search Performance Insights Blazly analyzes search performance metrics collected from Google Search Console. Performance analysis may include: Organic search visibility Search impressions Click performance Click-through rate (CTR) Average ranking positions Query-level performance trends These insights help users understand how their website performs in search results. Index Coverage Monitoring The audit system evaluates indexing data to identify pages that may not be properly indexed. Coverage analysis may include: Indexed pages Excluded pages Crawled but not indexed URLs Indexing warnings Index coverage opportunities This helps users identify issues that could limit search visibility. Technical SEO Evaluation Blazly reviews technical SEO signals that can affect search engine crawling and indexing. The evaluation may include: Crawl accessibility Indexability checks Sitemap validation Search Console warnings Technical issue detection SEO best-practice compliance Technical findings help users improve website accessibility for search engines. Actionable Recommendations Based on audit findings, Blazly generates recommendations designed to improve SEO performance. Recommendations may focus on: Indexing improvements Content optimization opportunities Technical SEO fixes Search visibility enhancements Performance improvements Website health corrections Recommendations are prioritized based on their potential impact. Project-Based Audits SEO Audit operates at the connected website or project level. This allows users to: Monitor SEO performance for specific websites Review audit data for individual projects Track website optimization efforts Maintain separate audit records across multiple properties Audit Reporting Blazly consolidates collected SEO data into an easy-to-understand audit report. Reports help users: Identify SEO issues Understand search performance Monitor indexing health Review optimization opportunities Prioritize SEO improvements The audit report serves as a centralized SEO performance dashboard. Integration Access If Google Search Console has not been connected, the audit section displays a connection prompt. Users can access: Go to Integrations Connect Google Search Console Verify website access Enable audit functionality SEO Audit becomes available once a valid Search Console property is connected.",
