        searchText: "Workspaces Located in the left navigation menu under the Workspace section. Workspaces provide a centralized environment for organizing, managing, and collaborating on content production activities. They help teams structure content workflows, group related projects, and streamline blog creation processes within a dedicated workspace. Workspaces are designed to support content operations at scale by providing a dedicated area for managing blogs, strategies, and content pipelines. Features Create Workspace Allows users to create a new workspace for organizing content projects and workflows. Each workspace acts as an independent environment where users can manage content production activities without affecting other projects. Workspace Name Each workspace is assigned a unique name that helps identify and differentiate content projects. Workspace names can be used to organize content based on: Clients Brands Campaigns Products Business units Content categories Workspace Repository Displays all created workspaces in a centralized location. Users can quickly access, manage, and navigate between multiple workspaces from a single interface. Content Organization Workspaces help structure content production by grouping related assets and activities together. This enables users to maintain clear separation between different content initiatives and marketing campaigns. Collaboration Management Provides a dedicated environment for teams to collaborate on content creation and planning activities. Team members can work within the same workspace to manage content workflows and maintain project alignment. Workspace Dashboard Each workspace serves as a management hub for content production activities. The workspace dashboard provides visibility into: Active content projects Content workflows Publishing activities Content organization Workspace Counter Displays the total number of workspaces currently created within the account. This provides a quick overview of active content environments being managed. Workspace Management Workspaces enable users to maintain a structured content production process by separating projects into dedicated environments. This helps: Improve content organization. Manage multiple projects efficiently. Streamline content operations. Maintain project-specific workflows. Support team collaboration. Empty State When no workspaces have been created, the page displays a No Workspaces Yet message along with a Create Your First Workspace action button. This provides users with a direct starting point for setting up their content management environment and organizing future content workflows. Integrations Integrations Located in the left navigation menu under the Workspace section. Integrations allow users to connect external platforms, content management systems, analytics tools, and publishing endpoints directly with Blazly. These integrations enable content publishing, performance analysis, website management, and workflow automation from a single platform. Connected integrations can be used across content generation, SEO analysis, publishing workflows, and automated content distribution. Features Connected Integrations Counter Displays the total number of active integrations currently connected to the account. This provides a quick overview of all connected publishing and analytics platforms. Google Search Console Google Search Console integration provides access to website performance and search visibility data directly within Blazly. This integration is required for: SEO Audit Page Speed Analysis Keyword Performance Analysis Search Visibility Monitoring Search Analytics Reporting Connect GSC Allows users to securely connect their Google Search Console account through OAuth authentication. Once connected, Blazly can access verified website properties and retrieve performance data for analysis tools. Search Performance Data After connection, Blazly can access: Search impressions Clicks Click-through rate (CTR) Average ranking positions Search queries Website performance insights CMS Integrations CMS Integrations allow users to connect website platforms directly with Blazly for content publishing and management. Webflow Allows users to connect Webflow websites to Blazly. Connected Webflow sites can be used for: Content publishing Blog deployment Website content management Automated publishing workflows Add Site Connects a Webflow website to Blazly and makes it available for publishing operations. WordPress Allows users to connect WordPress websites directly with Blazly. Connected WordPress sites can be used to publish generated content without requiring manual content transfer. Add Site Connects a WordPress website and authorizes Blazly to manage content publishing activities. GoHighLevel Allows users to connect GoHighLevel locations and websites through OAuth authentication. Connected GoHighLevel accounts can receive content generated within Blazly and support direct publishing workflows. Connect Initiates the OAuth connection process and authorizes Blazly to access the selected GoHighLevel account. Direct Blog Publishing Once connected, users can publish blog content directly to supported GoHighLevel websites without leaving Blazly. Webhook Integration Webhook Integration enables content publishing to virtually any platform that supports HTTPS webhooks. This integration is designed for advanced publishing workflows and third-party automation platforms such as: Zapier Make n8n Custom APIs Internal publishing systems Proprietary CMS platforms HTTPS Webhook URL Allows users to configure a destination webhook endpoint where content payloads will be delivered. The webhook receives structured JSON data whenever content is published through Blazly. Fixed Blazly Bridge URL Provides a persistent inbound endpoint generated by Blazly. This bridge URL can be used when external systems require a stable endpoint while Blazly forwards requests to the configured webhook destination. Override URL for Test Only Allows users to temporarily specify an alternative webhook endpoint for testing purposes without modifying the saved production webhook configuration. Save Webhook Stores the webhook configuration for future publishing operations. Saved webhook settings can be reused across multiple content publishing workflows. Send Test JSON Sends a sample payload to the configured webhook endpoint. This allows users to validate: Endpoint connectivity Payload structure Automation workflows Third-party integrations before using live publishing. Webhook Payload The test payload contains sample content data structured similarly to live publishing events. Payloads may include: URL Title Meta Title Meta Description Content (HTML) Primary Keyword Publishing Metadata Send to Webhook Once configured, users can publish content directly to the connected webhook endpoint from supported areas of the platform, including: My Blogs Bulk Publishing Workflows Automated Content Distribution Pipelines This enables fully automated publishing workflows across external platforms and services.",
